Build system

  • Cargo — the Rust package manager
    • BurntSushi/cargo-benchcmp88 8 [cargo-benchcmp] — utility to compare Rust micro-benchmarks

    • mmstick/cargo-deb125 5 — generate binary Debian packages

    • maxsnew/cargo-dot37 10 — generate graphs of a Cargo project's dependencies
    • cardoe/cargo-ebuild22 2 [cargo-ebuild] - cargo extension that can generate ebuilds using the in-tree eclasses
    • killercup/cargo-edit326 46 [cargo-edit] — allows you to add and list dependencies by reading/writing to your Cargo.toml file from the command line
    • Ralvke/cargo-find [cargo-find] — Find crates from command line
    • kbknapp/cargo-graph65 9 [cargo-graph] — updated fork of cargo-dot with additional features
    • imp/cargo-info [cargo-info] — queries crates.io for crates details from command line
    • sagiegurari/cargo-make111 9 [cargo-make] — Rust task runner and build tool.
    • regexident/cargo-modules96 4 [cargo-modules] — A cargo plugin for showing a tree-like overview of a crate's modules.
    • imp/cargo-multi [cargo-multi] — runs specified cargo command on multiple crates
    • kbknapp/cargo-outdated131 19 [cargo-outdated] — displays when newer versions of Rust dependencies are available, or out of date
    • sunng87/cargo-release76 8 [cargo-release] — tool for releasing git-managed cargo project, build, tag, publish, doc and push
    • DanielKeep/cargo-script155 11 [cargo-script] — lets people quickly and easily run Rust "scripts" which can make use of Cargo's package ecosystem
    • greyblake/cargo-testify35 3 [cargo-testify] — watches files changes, runs tests and notifies about the result with friendly OS notification
    • nabijaczleweli/cargo-update150 23 [cargo-update] — cargo subcommand for checking and applying updates to installed executables
    • passcod/cargo-watch290 39 [cargo-watch] — utility for cargo to compile projects when sources change
